<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1838,2007]" lastBlockId="27.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,500,1946,1971]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[508,756,1948,1971]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Potamites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="juruazensis">
<emphasis box="[508,756,1948,1971]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Potamites juruazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to southwestern 
<taxonomicName box="[1083,1201,1946,1971]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="26" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, with its distribution until now restricted to a few localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[625,693,1982,2007]" name="Brazil" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[752,806,1983,2006]" name="Peru" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Peru</collectingCountry>
, associated with the Juruá, Urucu, and Camisea Rivers (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1237,1259]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,313,1210]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,303,1215]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Distribution of examined material of Neusticurus bicarinatus, N. racenisi, and Potamites juruazensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581991/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[302,373,151,176]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[741,859,152,176]" country="Peru" name="Amazonas" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[919,977,152,176]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Acre</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1240,153,176]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Potamites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="juruazensis">
<emphasis box="[990,1240,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Potamites juruazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits the leaf litter of low primary forest, not directly associated with streams (Ávila-Pires &amp; Vitt 1998; Vitt &amp; Ávila-Pires 1998; Icochea 
<emphasis box="[528,584,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">et al.</emphasis>
2001).
</paragraph>
